      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__CRYPTO__AES__FUNCTIONS_1gaf508565bc1ffbe903d3496a7b712dd2f" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>sl_status_t</type>
        <definition>sl_status_t sl_si91x_aes</definition>
        <argsstring>(sl_si91x_aes_config_t *config, uint8_t *output)</argsstring>
        <name>sl_si91x_aes</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="structsl__si91x__aes__config__t" kindref="compound">sl_si91x_aes_config_t</ref> *</type>
          <declname>config</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>uint8_t *</type>
          <declname>output</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>To encrypt or decrypt the message according to the given configuration. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This is a blocking API. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">config</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Configuration object of type <ref refid="structsl__si91x__aes__config__t" kindref="compound">sl_si91x_aes_config_t</ref> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">output</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Buffer to store the output. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The maximum length of the message in bytes that can be handled in one go is determined by SLI_SI91X_MAX_DATA_SIZE_IN_BYTES_FOR_AES. If the message length is not a multiple of SL_SI91X_AES_BLOCK_SIZE, the function returns an error.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>sl_status_t. For more information on status codes, refer to <ulink url="https://docs.silabs.com/gecko-platform/latest/platform-common/status">SL STATUS DOCUMENTATION</ulink>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
